      highlights:['Al-Shabaab (Somalia-based Islamist militants) has conducted attacks on Kenyan soil, including hotels, shopping centres (Westgate Mall 2013, DusitD2 Hotel 2019), and churches in Nairobi.','Do Not Travel to: North Eastern Kenya (Mandera, Wajir, Garissa counties) — active Al-Shabaab insurgency and violent banditry.','Do Not Travel to: The Kenya–Somalia border zone and the coastal strip between Mombasa and the Somali border.','Reconsider Travel to: Lamu County (despite being a tourist destination — periodic Al-Shabaab attacks and kidnappings).','Nationwide anti-government protests (June–August 2024 anti-Finance Bill protests) resulted in deaths and the storming of Parliament. Exercise care if political demonstrations are occurring.','Petty crime in Nairobi (particularly Central Business District, Eastlands) and Mombasa is significant. Mugging and phone snatching are common.','INTERPOL has coordinated multiple major wildlife trafficking and poaching operations involving Kenyan networks.'],
